Business Brief -- Hoechst AG:
   Polypropylene Plant Slated
   To Close by Chemical Firm
The 173 workers employed at the plant will be offered jobs
elsewhere in the company or be asked to accept early
retirement, Hoechst said.
   Hoechst's capacity for polypropylene production in all of
Western Europe is 520,000 tons a year. The company has plants
in Germany, France and Spain.